docs.lead_paragraph: Thomas C. Dawson's "The South Arner- lean Republics," which G.P. Putnam's Sons have in preparation, in two volumes, will occupy a place in the publishers Story of the Nations Series. Mr. Degrain is Secretary or the United States Legation in Brazil, and may therefore be supposed to be in a position to secure special information, or, at any rate, to make careful observation.

docs.snippet: GERMANY'S expansion policy in South and Central America has drawn the attention of thoughtful citizens of this country for some considerable time. About as many statements have appeared magnifying as belittling it. What are the real facts in the...
docs.lead_paragraph: GERMANY'S expansion policy in South and Central America has drawn the attention of thoughtful citizens of this country for some considerable time. About as many statements have appeared magnifying as belittling it. What are the real facts in the case? An answer to that question, marshaling the main elements, will show in how far this Nation has reason for disquiet.

docs.lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON, April 21. -- Considerable attention is being given in official and diplomatic circles to the embarrassing position which Germany is forced to occupy at Washington as a result of the delay in the arrival of the credentials of Baron Speck von Sternburg, who, it has been announced, is eventually to succeed Herr von Holleben as Ambassador here.
